    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nPlease change the default snippet behaviour; considering that it is not documented anyways and neovim is not v1.0, now's the time.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n\n* Do not automatically exit snippet mode when reaching the final \"tabstop\", which prevents one from going back from the last \"tabstop\". Instead, make it behave like any other \"tabstop\" location meaning exit snippet mode when exiting insert mode. Current behaviour is especially problematic because:\n* There is no indication on which \"tabstop\" you are in. Please add this info to the statusbar like so: `2/3`, maybe with a prefix \"snip:\" or even nesting info: \"snip^1:\". Not all \"tabstop\" locations have placeholder text thus it is impossible to determine the number of locations visually; moreover this would also indicate whether you are in snippet mode or not.\n* Use different default maps to allow inserting tabs. For example `<a-n>` to expand and go to next \"tabstop\", `<a-p>` to go to previous \"tabstop\".\n",
    "closed_at": null,
